1) For installing the haskell platform on linux, use the command given below
sudo apt-get install haskell-platform
2) Type this command in terminal to compile the file hello.hs with a machine code file named hello
ghc -o hello hello.hs
3) Type this command to run the compiled file named hello (on Windows OS it is a bit different)
./hello
4) Type this command to compile a file named A.hs with -threaded and optimizations on
ghc -O2 --make A.hs -threaded -rtsopts
5) Type this command to run the compiled file named "A" on two cores and show the time it took to process the output
time ./A +RTS -N2
6) Type ghci in terminal to open the interpreter for quick scripting
